<H2><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C"><B>PRAYER OF THANKSGIVING FOR PENITENTIAL CELEBRATIONS</B></FONT></H2>
<H4><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C"><I></I></FONT></H4>
<H3><PRE>
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    G                Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P.  The Lord be with you.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    G             Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  And with your spirit.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    F             E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P.  Lift up your hearts.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    F                       E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  We lift them up to the Lord.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    E7                                 Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P.  Let us give thanks to the Lord our God.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       G            Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  It is right and just. (2) 

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Am           Dm        Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P.  It is indeed right and just,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    E                                  Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    it is our duty and leads to our salvation
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                      Dm               Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    to give you thanks always and everywhere,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    E                      Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    almighty and merciful God.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    F                           Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    How wonderfully you created man 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    F                                 E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    and still more wonderfully remade him.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Am                      G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    You do not abandon the sinner,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                     Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    but seek him out with a Father's love.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    You sent your Son into the world
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                     Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    to destroy death and sin by his Passion
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                             G              Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    and to restore life and joy by his Ressurection.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                       G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    You sent the Holy Spirit into our hearts
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                               Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    to make us your children and heirs of your Kingdom.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                               G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    You constantly renew our spirit 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                        Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    in the sacraments of your redeeming love,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    freeing us from slavery to sin
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">             F           
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    and transforming us
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                       E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    into the likeness of your beloved Son.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">     Am                        G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  Freeing us from slavery to sin
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">             F
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    and transforming us
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                       E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    into the likeness of your beloved Son.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Am                             G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P.  We thank you and bless you, O Lord,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                             Am 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    for the wonders of your mercy;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                 G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    and we join with the whole Church
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                       Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    in a new song of praise.
</PRE></H3>

